      "span_text": "In addition, satellites in LEO, located at approximately 700 km, turn a full Earth in approximately 95 minutes, which means that the point on Earth to which the satellite is pointed will move with respect to the objective at 7 km per second; the pointing process is governed by the ADCS that guarantees the RS system pointing target for a short time period."
